To make the dressing, combine the egg, egg yolk, mustard, and lemon zest and juice in a food processor. Slowly add the oil. Add the dill and season. Transfer to a bowl, cover, and refrigerate. Combine the red onion and vinegar in a bowl. Let stand for 10 minutes. Drain well. Remove the lobster meat from the shell, and chop it in large chunks. Divide the watercress among 4 plates, and add the fennel, onion, tomatoes, and lobster; drizzle with the dressing. Serve with more dressing served on the side. 3. Remove the lobster meat from the shell, and chop it in large chunks. 4. Divide the watercress among 4 plates, and add the fennel, onion, tomatoes, and lobster; drizzle with the dressing. Serve with more dressing served on the side.